{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UeVGC57UaVDzEsVQQXgjst","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The ConfigMap `change-plan` has been created with a 14 KB plan. The live cluster is completely unchanged.\n\nHere's a summary of what was found and documented:\n\n---\n\n**Current cluster state (observed, not changed):**\n- 3-node StatefulSet, all on **Elasticsearch 8.11.1**, JDK 21.0.1, 512 MiB heap, 1 Gi container limit\n- One index `test-index` — 1 shard, 1 replica, tier preference `data_content`\n- No custom cluster settings, no custom ILM policies, no snapshot repository\n- **Critical gap:** `xpack.security.enabled: false` — security was disabled after initial deployment. The TLS secret (`es-http-tls`) and certs still exist, but the cluster accepts plaintext HTTP. The Ingress enforces HTTPS externally but traffic inside the cluster is unencrypted.\n- `elastic-password-next` secret exists alongside `elastic-password` — a password rotation is in an incomplete state\n- `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is still set (should be removed after bootstrap)\n\n**Migration plan covers (in priority order):**\n1. Resolve the in-flight password rotation (decide keep/abort `elastic-password-next`)\n2. Re-enable `xpack.security` + TLS (restore the original intended config using existing `es-http-tls` secret)\n3. Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from elasticsearch.yml\n4. Increase container memory limit to 2 Gi (OS memory is at 94–95%)\n5. Configure a snapshot repository and take a pre-upgrade snapshot\n6. Rolling image upgrade 8.11.1 → 8.12.x with shard allocation disabled during the window\n7. Post-upgrade: ILM for test-index, CPU limits, tighten auto-create-index"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":343,"cache_read_input_tokens":49446,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":343},"output_tokens":